data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home décor at your Tucson, AZ Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
order randomly canceled I'm moving my dad to a retirement home in Tucson and having to handle the arrangements from out of state. I got on a chat with a sales person in the store who was fabulous. Helped me pick out exactly what my dad needed, made sure it was in stock, and arranged for delivery and assembly in time to have it ready for the move. Then two days later and now 8 days before the move, I got an email that the entire order was canceled. I called the number on the email to sort it out, that lead me to someone who told me I needed to talk to customer service. So basically hang up and call back, have to try to bully my way through the chatbot AGAIN to try to get a person on the phone. This took half an hour but I did eventually get a live person on the phone. She recommended that I go through the entire process of ordering online again and hey maybe this time I'll work out. That or walk into a location and buy it in person, then arrange for delivery. Again, I am in another state which is why I was buying furniture online. Apparently I'm the first person in the history of furniture to have a delivery address different from my billing address and they simply did not have the ability to cope with such wild anarchy. The good news is that IKEA does so I have furniture on the way from Tempe AND I'm sure that some loss prevention team is super chuffed about having prevented this obvious fraudulent attempt to purchase furniture. so hey Ashley thanks so much for making an already stressful situation soooo much worse

BEWARE! We bought a Sealy mattress here for about $1200. The salesperson said we had 30 days to return if we didn't like it. We believed it because every mattress company we looked at offered at least 30 days, most 90 to 180 days to return if we weren't satisfied (including Sealys website) The mattress was extremely uncomfortable and activated my sciatica causing me to eventually miss nearly a month of work, dr's visits, physical therapy etc. I called Ashley customer service and was told i needed to send pictures of the mattress. Ok, even though the mattress wasn't defective it's their process so i sent them. No word from them for a week, and i'm sleeping on an air mattress. I called back and they told me they had to send a technician out to look at the mattress. To See What?? They then told me they offer no return policy but i could go to the location directly and talk with someone there. I did, asked for a manager and spoke to C. Templeton. I rarely get to speak to a salesperson as uninterested in helping me as he was. When I told him his salesperson said we could return it if it wasn't comfortable he told me they would re-educate their salespeople. How does that help me? He made no effort to find a way to help or take responsibility for their salespersons misinformation. No offer to contact the manufacturer, no offer to help in any way. So, since you can buy the same mattress anywhere with guarantees, why buy one from a company that won't take returns?

Order #19A***520. On May 20th, 2024, we purchased over $8,000 worth of furniture from Jamie Suarez in the Tucson Ashley location. Mr. Suarez placed an item on our bill (a desk, item 11743-34) that we did not ask for and in no way wanted. We attempted to get Mr. Suarez to correct the bill, remove the error and provide us with a new receipt, this seems to be beyond Mr. Suarez's ability and competencies to accomplish. Mr. Suarez had Agatha Anhill email us a receipt, it was supposed to be an updated receipt but it was NOT, it was simply an identical receipt, still in error. Further, the receipt Ms. Anhill provided was so small that it could not be read without the use of a magnifying glass and of course the receipt was the original, not a corrected copy. I texted Mr. Suarez 12 times for a new receipt, he will no longer return my texts. I have called the store 10 times; they do not answer. To date we not received an updated receipt and we don't know if they removed the item (desk) from our purchase. The store is impossible to deal with, even something this simple, they have zero customer service. We have not received our shipment yet and already regret this shame of an operation. But the fun doesn't stop there. During our purchase at Ashley we found that numerous items on their website cannot be purchased in the store, in fact, Mr. Suarez told us that the store and the website are not coordinated together or connected. Further, they had a store display of a Polywood type table and chairs that we wanted but it was no longer stocked (they kept displaying it anyway). Then Mr. Suarez told me that we could have the store display for 20% off but I would need to unbolt it (hundreds of bolts and heavy/bulky) and take it with me. Do NOT shop at Ashley, they are incompetent, uncaring and void of customer service.

Where do I begin with this nightmare? I only gave Ashley one star but really it should be a negative 5 stars. My mother bought a very nice desk on April 18th. Twelve days later a broken desk is delivered. The electronics did not work. The delivery guys said they would call it in. A phone call is received right away from customer service but it will be over a month to get a tech out to look at the desk. After much arguments, customer service tells us someone will come out on May 4th. No one showed. My mother has to go to the store and find someone to return the desk. BUT we are now told we can't get a refund until a tech come out and make a determination on the status of the desk and even then we can only pick out a different desk. Why no refund? Because so much time had passed from purchase date. Well it took two weeks for delivery! Shouldn't the clock start ticking from delivery date? We are stuck with a desk we don't want and doesn't work and maybe just maybe a tech will show up on the 15th. This is the poorest customer service I have ever witnessed. The store new immediately there was a problem but Ashley doesn't care!

Hello all, I'm not one to leave negative reviews however dealing with this Ashley Furniture store has been one of the least satisfactory customer service experiences I have ever dealt with. I will not necessarily knock the furniture itself, I believe it's a good deal for the price, however buyer beware. 4 months ago I went into this store and selected a few items of furniture as I had just moved to the area, we purchased a few items of furniture and I was told that the wait would be at most 4 weeks. After waiting patiently for four weeks, I went into the store to inquire about my delivery. It turns out that without notice the store claimed that the floor they had just had on the showroom floor was discontinued. This all without any notification or plan for reimbursement or accommodation. In addition they told me that since I had done business with them through a lender that they could no longer accept any payment. This is all without any concrete explanation or accomnodation. In addition to this I see that they are running effectively the same piece of furniture on the showroom floor. I came in again a few weeks later to bring this issue up again. Now they had reversed course and said that they could credit my account and resolve any balances on the account as needed (why not in the first place). This time I was able to two months later resolve the issue which honestly should have been resolved from day one, I was given a delivery date and confirmed with the service representative there at the store for a few weeks later. Except no the Ashley Warehouse operations sent an email in the middle of the night to "confirm" said appointment after it had already been confirmed. When I recieved the email I clicked the link to confirm however the "offer" expired. This leads me to believe that the Warehouse operations team is trying to scam customers in order to lighten their own loads or that maybe they can't accomodate their current volume which is a fail from multiple angles. No worries I go in to reschedule for another delivery date weeks later and set the date begrudgingly I might add. I get another email to rescedhule this time for my original date because suddenly their free. Guess what nothing arrives, no phone call, no text, no email , no notification. We are on month five for a piece of furniture that is widely produced by the store and currently now apparently without another delivery date. What is Ashley Furniture store doing exactly with their accounts. Guys, I got the "bad" end of the stick here for sure, and am dealing with perhaps unhealthy backorder log but what is going on with the Arizona branches here is very clear and it is clear that their entire corps of management, operations, and warehouse, is completely failing to get the JOB done. I request that every manager and supervisor of every division within the state of Arizona be promptly fired for negligence.

I’m literally standing in the old Sam Levitz store now as I type this because of how annoyed I am . This is now an Ashley owned furniture store on Pantano. I Ordered couch Dec 2 2023 and I still don’t have couch. They told me Jan, Feb, March and now April. Cross your fingers everyone! Worse part there’s been NO communication at all. I have reached out every time. You call store and they NEVER pick up. This has led me to have to drive to store every time I need to talk to someone. Their call center seems to be overseas and there’s major disconnect between local store and call centers.when I came to store to ask when my stuff coming they said I have financial hold and it can’t be delivered. Well ok… why didn’t anyone call me? Apparently Ashley policy is different compared to Sam Levitz per their sales manager and full payment needs to be made. I originally had deposit based on old policy. Like I said they are terrible at communications with their customers. A lady by me is complaining in the store about the same thing. I was met with lack of empathy and no sense of importance at all when I came in and that’s why I’m writing this. You need better training because your people look stress, barely smile and are obviously overwhelmed otherwise they just have bad attitude. I was told by customer service I they submitted a request for discount for my inconvenience. Came to the store and they said no because they have people who ordered in July and still have no furniture. Well you should be ashamed and offer discounts to them too!! Guess what… another gentlemen just walked up to desk with same issue. Take care of your customers during acquisition. Your process issues are your issue and not your customers spending money and supporting the business. At least have empathy and care from higher ups to people on the floor.

Update #4: (5/14/24) I still have not received my refund. And the BBB has still not heard from Ashley Furniture after numerous messages to them. Update #3: (4/23/24) I have not received my refund checks. I have not heard from Ashley furniture and the BBB has not received a response from Ashley Furniture either. This is very concerning. At this point, I will need to contact an attorney to help me with this situation. Update #2: (4/10/24) I still have not received my refund checks. I filed a complaint with the BBB on April 1st, and the BBB has indicated they have not heard from Ashley Furniture yet either. Ashley Furniture is a HORRIBLE company. I just want my $781.54 back. Update: I still have not received my refund checks from Ashley/Sam Levitz. I have now submitted a complaint with the BBB. I wish I could give negative stars. On Nov 14, 2023 I put a down payment on a couch. I was told that the couch I purchased would be in stock on Dec 10, 2023. I finished paying it off on Dec 7, 2023. I was then told after finishing my purchase, that the couch was on back order until mid December. Mid December came around and my salesman called me and said it would be end of Dec/early Jan. Every time I called, I would get the same excuse, still on back order. On March 8, 2024, the Asst. Manager called me saying that the couch was actually discontinued and blamed the previous owner (Sam Levitz) for the issue. I was told I could get my money back or get a different couch with the $781.54 credit I had. I went in the store the next day and picked a different couch. I had a difference of $78.07 owed to me after the purchase. They of course have no idea who is sending out the return checks. They said it would be mailed to me. I still have not received that check for the difference. On top of that, last week on the 21st of March, I received an email confirming the delivery of my couch for yesterday the 25th. The couch was not delivered and no one called me to tell me it wouldn't be delivered. After multiple unanswered calls to Ashley yesterday, I finally spoke to someone and they said it would be another week. I've heard that before. So I went down to Ashley last night and asked for a return of my money. I am now owed $703.47 and they don't know when I will receive that money either. I will be leaving a bad review with the BBB also. And if I don't receive my money ($781.54) soon, I will be making a complaint with the BBB.

UPDATE #2- Given Delivery date of 4/5/2024 no confirmation email no delivery tracking, were told we are not on the schedule and no one can tell us where our furniture is and can we even reschedule. Spoke to "Escalation" team and they were clueless on how to handle situation. They have offered to call back for three days and not one call back to explain what is going on and where my things are. Have already submitted another complaint with the Attorney Generals office. UPDATE: 4/03/2024 - 4 months still no furniture. Confirmed Delivery date for 4/3/2024 and they no showed and no call! UNBELIEVABLE! THEY ARE FRAUDS AND LIARS. DO NOT DO BUSINESS HERE. NO COMMUNICATION ORDERED DEC 27,2024----DO NOT BUY FROM HERE! Third Party Store. This is not and Ashley Direct Store. Fraudulent Business Practices. Fake delivery dates to get you buy and then change dates and don't notify. Waited three months from date they promised delivery and not one notification to say they were changing or why it was being held up. Location no longer answers phone, you get a customer service outsourced line since they do unethical business they cannot face their customers. Reported to Attorney General and store has history of fraudulent business practices along with no longer doing business with Synchrony Credit Card due to baiting customers into credit lines and fees not disclosed to them during purchases. BE CAREFUL WHEN GOING HERE. They will try to whatever they can to sell you the world but they will fall short on every promise including getting your order right. Order was even wrong and they wanted to recharge more delivery and setup fees even after it was their underwriting mistake. Check your order before they put it in, during, after, then call a few days and even a month after and you will see its changed and wrong. SAVE YOURSELF DO NOT BUY FROM THIS ASHLEY. GO TO ASHLEY ONLINE OR ASHLEY DIRECT. THIS IS A THIRD PARTY AND THEY ARE THIEVES AND UNETHICALLY RUN. THEIR MANAGERS ARE JOKES AND CANNOT AND WILL NOT DO ANYTHING TO HELP. BEWARE!!

Went in on Presidents’ Day to buy a dining room table and chairs. They were having system issues because of the switch to being only Ashley and getting all new systems, cool no big deal. They couldn’t get the system to work so they could swipe my card, no problem. So they wrote my card information down to pay for the order when the system was back up, no biggie if I had extra funds taken I’d know exactly who to report. Come to find out, they took my money and never even submitted the order. Called back and talked with Ashley. Took her forever to find my draft order (I’m assuming it was a draft since they never actually submitted it)? Finally found it, let me know it was actually submitted now, and told me they couldn’t deliver it until 2 weeks after I was supposed to receive it. Asked her if I could get a refund on my delivery charge due to the inconvenience they caused. Ashley said she’d speak with a manager and called me back. Never called me back. Had to call them back AGAIN and finally was offered the delivery fee refund. But I have to come in with my card physically for it to be refunded. Even though they had no issue taking my money without having the physical card. Can honestly say I will not be back, and I recommend people look for what they want and then buy it online to avoid the whole mess entirely.

The furniture is beautiful, a bit over priced I had quite a large order the first (which I ordered second) consisted of a 7 piece sectional, 4 stools, and a lift table. I ordered this mid July and did not receive the sectional until mid September. The stools I received them the following week after the purchase. My second order which I ordered first on July 5th was not delivered until September 23. We were not informed of any delays for anything other than the lift table. Delivery date kept getting pushed back due to "out of stock" or "supply chain issues."" The lift table was supposed to be new, I got the floor model a choice I made under the impression I'd be getting some of my money back for. I still have not received anything. I've called Ashley several times to be on hold for no less than 15 minutes, just waiting to be transferred to someone who never answered. For the price you pay, you'd expect a different level of service. Well, at least I do. They were quick to run the transaction but not quick to provide answers or to deliver the items purchased. Speaking of delivery, that team did great! The 7 piece sectional only came with 3 decorative pillows. Which I find odd for the size. The first order I placed was for a chaise, and that came with 4 pillows. I think the sales rep was good. I'm happy I don't have to buy furniture again in the near future, but even if I did, I'm not sure I'd be purchasing from Ashley. I just attached this photo to show how long I've been on hold when they called me! Update: I was only given 70 dollars out of 100 I was told when I purchased the floor model lift table. Customer service was like a 3 out of 10

Would not recommend shopping here if you can help it. We ordered a couch at the beginning of June. We were told it would be 2-4 weeks for delivery. Well it’s now August. We finally got a delivery date of today, so we hired a company to get rid of our old couch to make room for our new delivery. We go to check the status and can’t find anything. We then call and they tell us our sectional is on back order. Then why schedule a delivery date with us?! The issue is not necessarily the back order, but that we were scheduled a delivery date and time, so we got our old couch out, just for that to not be the truth. So we cancelled our order and are hoping for a full refund in the next couple of of days. We now have no living room furniture. This place was super disappointing. EDIT: I also just want to add that Ashley never contacted us after buying the couch. We called maybe 5 different times to figure out when our sectional would be ready. Ashley never contacted us to explain an additional delay for our delivery. And then today when our couch was mysteriously put on “back order” they still never contacted us about it. Just like the other reviews state, once they have your money, they have extremely poor customer service.

HORRIBLE! PLEASE DON'T GO! THEY BILL FOR FURNITURE THEY DON'T DELIVER AND NO ONE IS ABLE TO FIX ANYTHING. I AM TALKING ABOUT THOUSANDS OF DOLLARS BEING STOLEN FROM US - I bought furniture and they delivered furniture sets that were not purchased by us. I asked them to take it back and they billed my synchrony bank account for that furniture. I did not have the furniture in my possession. They never delivered my furniture that I bought initially. Yet 11 months after (now in July 2023) they still have not refunded my synchrony bank account. I tried filing a dispute with synchrony and they say that the store claims I still have the couches THAT I DO NOT HAVE. The delivery crew took everything back. I only have a dinning room table with 8 chairs. I have spoked to everyone in their customer service department including Victor a customer service manager who is now a sales man, Agatha another accounting customer service rep, their managers, and my original sales guy and none of them at the store have been able to help. I HOPE THE OWNER CAN READ THIS COMMENT AND REFUND ME MY MONEY!! I HAVE BEEN PAYING MY SYNCHRONY BANK ACCOUNT FOR I DON'T WANT MY CREDIT TO BE AFFECTED. PLEASE DON'T BUY AT THIS STORE THEY STEAL YOUR MONEY AND MAKE YOU WASTE VALUABLE TIME! PLEASE DON'T BUY ANYTHING HERE.

On 4.23.22 I purchased a loveseat from Ashley on Pantano. No problem with the sales at all. My concern is my scheduled delivery today 4.28.22 between 7am & 11am. Delivery called and left me a message at 9:30 and said they were on there way. My brother was here at my home and he said delivery guys were not outside. So I called and spoke to dispatch and was told that they were here outside. So I called my brother again and still nobody.( oh and I was told that they took pictures of what I had on my porch) So I then called my rental office and asked them to check if driver was outside in parking lot and I was told no... I then spoke to dispatch again and was told that the drivers left and that they would be back in 2 hours. I asked them to have the driver come after 3pm today and once I got home from work I called dispatch again and was told that the drivers attempted to deliver again. I never got a call that they were on there way and I asked if they can deliver now that I am home. Well now they want me to wait until Sunday to deliver and that I will receive a call to confirm Sundays deli ery.. I am not a happy camper.. I paid cash for my loveseat and I feel I should get reimbursed for the delivery charge. Oh and by the way, Ashley Furniture is affiliated with Sam Leviz. If I had known that I wouldn't of bought my loveseat Becuase I has bad experience with them years ago and have never went back to there store... Mary Ann Jesus

I had a great sales experience. Then my delivery day came and went with no phone call. I called and my table had been delayed. I understand there are a lot of supply chain issues currently. Delivery day came and the delivery people were amazing but there were parts missing. The table was left on Tuesday August 31st with the promise they would be back on September 3rd with the parts. I finally got a call on September 5th telling me that they don’t have my parts and don’t know when they will have them. Later that day I called the store back and my salesperson Sergio was excellent and tried to figure out what was going on, but was unsuccessful. Today September 14th I called the store again and asked to speak to a manager. I spoke to Brandon. He told me my problems were not a sales problem and there was nothing he could do for me. He then directed me to call the service department. When I told him that I’ve called there numerous times and left messages and no one has called me back, he said “that’s the same number I have to call, I don’t know what you want me to do.” It was very clear to me that he didn’t care at all and it was such a frustrating call that it end with me in tears. I would never recommend this store to anyone. All I want is for them to come get the table and give me my money back.

This is the second time we have ordered from this store and location. The first time we ordered a bed set and coffee table...was told it would take 2 weeks. Noone ever contacted us to let us know the delay we had to call numerous times to get any information. About 2 months later items were delivered. Went back a year later to purchase a sofa, we were told it would take 2 weeks again, I explained the original scenario to the saleswoman she confirmed that would not be the case as it would be available end of April at the latest May 9th. However, I got a phone call today and now it is going to be mid May and with a possiblity of being delayed longer. When someone asks what is a delivery time frame because we don't want to wait 2 months for furniture BE HONEST, don't lie to get the sale! We could have now gone somewhere else, this company is TERRIBLE when it comes to time frame, delivery and being TRANSPARENT about when the items are available. When we come in and say we want something that is in stock today...show us items in stock so we are not waiting. When you know this is what we are worried about and reassure us it will be only a couple weeks knowing that it isn't true...not good sales service!

The sales aspect was a good experience, knowledgeable & professional. The delivery was anything but that. First we're given a 3-hour window when to expect them, followed up by a phone message stating they would be there in 15-20 minutes. They arrived under 5 minutes. Two young men, who didn't see that I had cleared a path from our driveway through the carport to the front door to bring up the furniture, instead they marched straight through the front yard to the front door. When I spend over $3,000 for a mattress I expect it to be handled with care, instead only one man attempted to carry it, by himself, all the way & just before he got to the front door, he dropped it. After they set it up they rushed out the door. I had to run after them catching them in their truck to remind them they were expected to take the old mattress away. A very common procedure for Sam Levitz/Ashley stores. They both acted surprised, stating that wasn’t on their work order. Reluctantly they rushed back in, each grabbing an item, one the mattress & the other the box spring & rushed out dragging the items through the front yard. Refer to the photos below. I contacted Sam Levitz/Ashley about the incident & they apologized. No offer of a monetary compensation. I’ll be very hesitant to shop in their stores unless it’s an item I can take home myself & not have to rely on their amateur delivery service.

HORRIBLE, HORRIBLE CUSTOMER SERVICE! They will easily pick up your furniture, when you tell them to come get it, but they can't deliver the rest of your furniture. I understand we are in a Pandemic, but waiting 4 to 5 months for 4 chairs to arrive is ridiculous. Bought a dining room table and 6 chairs at the end of September, and was told my ETA would be early October. October comes around, and I got a phone call saying half your order is in, but the other half will be in another month, but don't worry before Thanksgiving. Every month they have called me or not called me to tell me some ridiculous story of where the chairs are cause it didn't arrive like they said in November. I called and asked to speak with a manager and no one picked up. I called again, and got a voicemail that was full. I called for the third time and got Jeff the assistant manager who told me good news and bad news, the chairs are at port, but they are at port. He said you will have them in mid- January and now here is mid January and he just called to say now the chairs are damaged, and it won't be till February or March! No family dinners at the table everyday, since I sold my other dining room table cause of your original delivery date. Thanks for letting us NOT celebrate the important family dinners like Thanksgiving and Christmas, cause your ETA was wrong and has been wrong since September. I already cancelled my ordered with Jeff today, but just wanted to write a review saying- I WILL NEVER BUY FROM ASHLEY FURNITUE AGAIN! MAYBE STOP SELLING MORE THAN YOU CAN GET IN!

I’ve shopped from Ashley’s in Texas and New Jersey and always had a great experience. I placed my order this time keeping the same experience in mind and trusted my order to be taken care of. However that has not been the case. First my delivery date was changed without consulting with me because the ottoman in my living room set was not available. If I was consulted I would’ve informed them that I can pick the ottoman myself when it is available. Next my delivery was not made because the apartment number was not listed on the delivery. At order time we discussed the apartment and the fact that there are two flights of stairs leading to my apartment. I called to have my delivery rescheduled and spoke to Alondra who promised to call me back in 20 minutes but has not done so yet after more than a day. I spoke the sales rep Michelle this afternoon who promised she will call back after speaking to the manager but has not done so as of yet. Calling the store or even the number listed for the owner on the bad reviews leads to a full inbox. I’m hoping someone will see this review and respond otherwise I will have to contact my credit card to cancel the order.

I ordered a dresser in mid-October. I was told the dresser would arrive during last week of November. I also ordered a bed in mid-November. I was told the bed would arrive with the dresser. No one called me back to confirm a delivery date throughout the month of November; I had to call customer service to follow up on the already late order. I was on hold for 20 min. I was told both items were already in. I asked why no one called me to schedule a delivery. Was given no answer as to why. I maintained my patience and calm, since I know delivery dates are a bit less reliable due to the pandemic. I set up a delivery for 12/15 between 2:00p and 6:00p. I told the delivery representative that I got off work at 2:30p and wouldn’t make home till 3:00p. I was told it wasn’t an issue, since they will call ahead of time to schedule a specific time. Keep in mind that now my order is 3 weeks late at this point. On 12/15, no one called me, and they arrived a bit before 2:00p. I was aware of this because I have a Ring video doorbell. I wasn’t home. I called customer service to ask why the delivery was so early. They said they already arrived and no one was home. I was told they would reschedule the delivery at 3:00p. I still maintained what little patience and calm I still had. No one showed up a 3:00p. I called back, and was told they were on their way. No one showed. I called back, and a manager told me it would be rescheduled to 12/16 3:00p – 6:00p. On 12/16, no one showed up between 3:00p – 6:00p. No one called me to let me know the order wouldn’t be arriving. I called customer service, and was told the order never went out in the first place and it was on hold. I was told they can deliver it on 12/22 between 2:00p – 6:00p. I said I work till 2:30p and couldn’t be home till 3:00p. I was told no guarantees they can make that window. I asked to speak with a manager, and I was told one would call me back. A manager ended up never calling me. I feel like no one cares about this, and I am really upset. I am still waiting for my furniture, and I am on the verge of canceling the order.

(Translated by Google) Very bad experience. A total lack of respect for the client. We made a purchase on 11/28/20 at the end of the "seller" tells us that the bed did not have the desired color, that he had made a mistake .. Well, we selected another color from those available. My husband, from Wednesday, 09/12/2020, contacted the seller since the delivery date is for 12/12/2020, and the delivery people still did not call us. And it turned out that they could not deliver on the agreed day from the purchase! How daring they are. If my husband did not call, we would not find out ... as if that were not enough it turns out that the alternate color of the bed is not available either ... Omg! Quite a disaster and we found out why we called and we insisted since Wednesday. 9/12/20 .. The manager answered the phone, yyyy nothing resolved. They called us later to offer "free" a basic frame "to which the bed arrives" ... how is it possible if the alternative color was available on the day of our shopping? and now that? Did they sell them too and didn't reserve the one we paid for? Too disorganized and disrespectful to the customer. (Original) Muy mala experiencia. Una falta al respeto total al cliente. Realizamos una compra el 11/28/20 al finalizar el "vendedor" nos dice que la cama no la había del color deseado, que se había equivocado.. Bueno, seleccionamos otro color de los disponibles. Mi esposo desde el día miércoles, 12/09/2020, se comunicó con el vendedor ya que la fecha de entrega es para el 12/12/2020, y aun no nos llamaban los de la entrega. Y resulto que ¡no podrían entregar el día acordado desde la compra! Que atrevidos son. Si mi esposo no llamaba, no nos enterábamos...como si eso fuese poco resulta que tampoco hay disponible el color alterno de la cama... Omg! Todo un desastre y nos enteramos por que llamamos he insistimos desde el miércoles. 12/9/20 .. El gerente atendió al teléfono, yyyy en nada resolvió. Nos llamaron más tarde para ofrecer "gratis" un frame básico "a lo que llega la cama"... ¿cómo es posible si el color altetno lo tenían disponible el día de nuestra compras? ¿y ahora que? ¿ Los vendieron también y no reservaron el que pagamos? Demasiada desorganizados y falta al respeto al cliente.

I really am not sure where to begin but the short version is "Buyer Beware" I'll start out with the positive: Our salesman Omar was absolutely excellent. His attention to detail, follow up and continuous communication is commendable and the only reason this review got any stars at all. Unfortunately, his excellence was overshadowed by a HORRIBLE delivery crew. On Black Friday we were in search of a decent dining table for our small family. We found an adequate table and proceeded to Omar to ring us up. While doing so, we decided on ordering a top of the line Tempur Pedic with adjustable base. Between the 2 items, were well into the $5,000 mark. We set delivery for December 7th (12 days later). On the 29th I was advised by Delivery that my mattress was in stock and just waiting for the base to be built but to expect express delivery sometime on the 3rd and that I'd receive a call to confirm the time. I did not receive a call so I called on the 11th and was told that the base was not available and now contradictory to what I was told, my mattress was now on "backorder." Through all the stress, Omar was always there answering questions I had and providing me reassurance. 12/7 rolls around and the delivery guy shows up! ...but only with sheets...for the bed that may or may not be on backorder. Later that day my table arrived. I was expecting 2 chairs and the table top as I was told that the other 2 chairs were backordered (no fault here, I was aware of this up front). What I got was a table, and only 1 chair that had a puncture to the leather. Delivery told me that they broke the other chair while building it. Now I'm expecting 4 new chairs and still have not yet (the 9th) been told when I'll be getting them. After getting the run around from the delivery team/warehouse and the final straw with getting a punctured chair and excuse about my 2nd one I finally had enough and cancelled my order. I, in good faith, cannot trust their warehouse/delivery team to deliver me a $5,000 mattress without incident, nor do I trust the warehouse to assemble my actuating bedframe correctly if they were able break a simple dining chair. Lastly, I need to mention that this is not the first run in with Ashley/Sam Levitz products and warehouse issues. That story was 2 years ago and unreviewed but it still doesn't seem that the back end of operations has gotten their stuff together.

Sales ladyWas very helpful for me and my husband to find the right couch for our new home. this was our first big purchase and we were very excited. While purchasing in beginning of September, she told us delivery would be Early October. Which we figured we would toughen it out even tho we do not have any couches... We patiently waited and waited. Once we called, they changed it to early November.. Waited and waited again, now it’s middle November and they’re saying delivery is middle december. Of course they have COVID to blame. But it’s all BS. My uncle received his couches weeks after placing the order. We want to cancel our order that way we can find faster delivery elsewhere, but not sure if they will ACTUALLY stick to delivering in December and not push it back to MARCH When you try and call in, they leave you on hold until you press 1 to leave a number for call back. Then they immediately call you back and hang up before you can answer. It’s an automated voice saying their mailbox is full. I've called them at least 5 times, and the same thing has happened repeatedly. I've never been able to connect with someone when I call directly, and have only had a successful call back once. Do I really have to drive down to the location to get the information I NEED that way I’m not hung up on every time ??? NOT THE SERVICE I expect FOR PAYING 2k on furniture. No excuses... UPDATE: After 3 months they delivered our sectional. We were very excited until receiving the WRONG LAYOUT of our sectional. Our sales rep did an excellent job at explaining how they consider the chaise lounge on the right or left side WHEN standing up, not sitting down. We even stood up with her to let her know the layout we wanted and she repeated it back to us a couple of times. I’m not sure how they made this mistake. Thankfully, customer service was nice enough to see if they had the correct pieces in stock.

Honestly one of the worst experiences I've ever had with a company for customer service. We ordered our furniture in September with it backdated until October. The salesperson never contacted us with updates like once we left, all their promises were unfulfilled. Its now November and we still haven't received our furniture. Call in to see where it is and the operator transfers us 7 times to the shipping department where it says to leave a message but the mailbox is full so its impossible. Call back again got the same operator who, even after we explained the full mailbox, transfers us again to the place where we can't leave a message. 7 different times. Same person. Then we finally get a representative on the line who speaks as if we're an inconvenience and gives us attitude after we explain why we're frustrated. Then get a "manager" on the line to tell us that we are at fault and we need to calm down because even though they didn't provide decent customer care, we are being rude by raising our voices to explain why their customer service was so horrible. The manager didn't even listen to my concerns, he just interrupted me multiple times and told me to calm down even when I spoke at a level tone. Honestly I have never experienced a company with as poor customer service as this and I can guarantee I will never shop here again.

My first time trying to buy nice furniture, what an absolute nightmare. If you’re thinking about ordering from this store, or any Ashley Furniture store, don’t do it. You’re going to pay thousands of dollars for literally nothing. TLDR; ordered in July and now it’s October, no furniture delivered (but still being billed for it) and the worst customer service experience ever. We ordered a bedroom set, mattress, and home office desk on 7/25. Were told we would have our stuff by the middle of August, which was fine because we understood Covid delays, etc. The same day our bed frame was going to be delivered in August, it was found to be “broken on the truck”. No big deal, we were told it would just be a week or two and we would get one. It’s October, still no bed frame, no desk, no dresser, and no updates from our sales person about when we will get it (Sharon makes her sale and then could care less about you). We have $1500 mattress we can’t use, but we sure are paying for it. Most recently, we were told the desk we ordered was discontinued, but we could have the floor model (no discount offered, of course). We agree to this, and the day it’s supposed to be delivered - you guessed it - it’s found to be “broken on the truck”. So we call to cancel our order and schedule having the furniture that has been delivered picked up, and are told to call customer service. We call customer service, they put us on hold, and then transfer us to a completely different Ashley location than the one we bought the furniture from. That representative can’t help us either, and we’re told we’ll “get a call back from a manager”. Still waiting on that call, and I won’t hold my breath that I’ll get it anytime soon. We wouldn’t have bought the furniture if we knew it would take literally months to receive it. Now the cancellation process looks like it’s going to be a hassle too. Stay away from doing business with this company, unless you have a truck and can walk away with the furniture that day. Order from Ikea, or literally any other company. Looking forward to the canned response from a Steve or a Jeff below this review pretending to care, with another useless phone number to call.

We've purchased from Ashley furniture many times and this is by far the worst experience with this company. The finance people are extremely rude to the sales staff and we witnessed an uncomfortable moment between them. Anyway that wasn't my comcern so Fast forward to end of August still no table, called to see the new ETA- was on hold for 30+ min and was told it wasn't in yet. I gave them the address of the new home we were purchasing and asked that It now be delivered there. They agreed, and gave me a new date of 9/24 TODAY 9/22 at 9am I got a call saying it would be delivered in 40 minutes!!! The house isn't ours until 3pm. I'm not going to leave the table outside! I called the delivery center and now I'm being told they can't deliver it on the 24th (as previously requested) and that the new date for delivery isn't until 9/28 I was so fed up that I called Ashley again and after being on hold for another 30min (again) told the lady to refund back my funds. She didn't seem the least bit bothered or slightly compassionate about my difficulties with the company. She simply said ok we can refund back the funds Anyway extremely disappointed.

Nice showroom but they need to work on customer service on the phone and in person,so my elderly mother has been trying to buy a queen size bed frame with headboard and it was being sold by Sam Levitz and every time my mother called 3 to 4 time's a day for 3 day's now Ashley's would answer the phone and my mother would ask for sam Levitz the person answering the phone (Ashley's worker) would tell my mother please hold and hung up the phone on my mother and my mom went through this for 4 calls the first day & 3 calls on the 2nd day and 4 calls on the 3rd day when I cam home to my mother crying because she's been trying to buy my daughter (her granddaughter)a bed frame cause I could only afford the mattress so I said don't worry mom I'll just go down there and pick it up stop crying it will be ok I was just there a month ago and it wazent that bad I tell her, so I go down to Sam Levitz and make my way to where the frame and headboard was and sales person informs me that none in stock here or at main warehouse but they do have 50 coming in and if I wanted the sale price I would have to pay now to get the sale price and wait for bedframe to come in late July, I said ok let me run to my house and let my mom know since it was her money and the sales person said ok I'll be rite here in this area I said ok great I'll be rite back in 10 or 15 minutes if she wants the deal and I leave and I come back and I go to the area where the sales person said they would be in and me and my son waited for like 20 minutes finnaly I went to the front main desk and front desk person was like I'll send a salesman over to that area and I was like well I'm here at the register and here's the paper with the item for sale can I just pay for it right here ? and front desk person was like no you need to go through a sales man and they'll meet you over there in a minute so my son and I make our way back to the bed area and stand there for like 15 minutes and finally I look towards the front of the building from the back and see what looks like the salesperson who was sapose to meet me 45 minutes ago and looked accros the show room floor at me as I'm looking at my watch and when I looked back and allmost got eye contact the salesperson turned around really quick and never saw her again and another 5 minutes went by and finally was rescued by a salesman passing by and if it wasn't for Mr. Birdsong I wouldn't have given you guy's any star's thanks to Kevin you guys are getting 3 , he totally handled the situation and assured me that when bedframe arrives on the 27th I can call him on 28th to pick up item,so to be continued and we will see if star's go up or down when I pick up bed frame on the 28th,till then thank you Kevin for your time and help.

And that's the last shipment because they are no longer manufacturing those items..... so if I dont receive that shipment I'm out of luck..... this is really ridiculous! I think I wouldnt even be so mad if SOMEONE AT LEAST CONTACTED ME WITH UPDATES!!! THIS IS VERY BAD CUSTOMER SERVICE. I WILL NEVER GONBACK TO THE SAME PERSON MICHAEL O'CONNER. I understand items are delay but to say the day I purchased my items that they were all in the warehouse available asap. And then they no longer our is BAD!!! And not to even bother informing me what's going on..... I wish I could give a 0 star instead of this 1 star.

Long story short, I purchased a queen mattress and headboard on 05/15/2020. After being in the store for about 20 minutes, Gilbert Leon approached me and was my salesman. I made my selection on what I wanted to buy. He placed my order, then tells me the mattress is on Backorder until the 21st of May. He should've mentioned this from the beginning. I said OK. I called Sam Levitz a total of 4 times about my backorder and every time I was told something different. They kept pushing back the ETA on the mattress. I texted Gilbert about my order on 06/01/2020, and he said it would be in the following week. When I didn't hear anything back, I texted him again following up on my order. No response. I called Sam Levitz AGAIN to get a status on my purchase and now I was told that the headboard is discontinued. WHY would I be sold an item that is discontinued? I finally went in the store on 6/14/2020 to see what I could do. Gilbert was there, I told him about my order, he told me to make another selection on the headboard and that the mattress was coming in on 6/18/2020. When I was ready to be helped Gilbert was with another customer and completely ignored me and my husband. I finally got so frustrated and went to the cashier to get my money back. I didn't want anyone from this store to get a commission on what I bought. Ashley has horrible customer service. All the salesman care about is making a buck, and have no genuine interest in their customer. I will never shop at Ashley or Sam Levitz again.

Quality of furniture and follow-up service is low, bordering scam-like. TL:DR at bottom. Spending a lot of money in store was very easy. I spent about 3.2k on furniture including the best warranties. I was initially very happy with my in store service. I had plans to return for bed sets and a few other items. This took a radical turn when I needed them to follow up their in-store promises. One piece of furniture, a sofa table, I tried to cancel delivery as they didn’t have it in stock for a month (longer than promised) and I had to pick up a different one in that amount of time. This took a month or so of calling twice a week, but it got done (Or so I thought). I shortly received a call that a desk, on the same order, had been waiting for a delivery address and date for an entire month. (This is after receiving several successful deliveries of my other furniture). The delivery people came with the desk and desk chair after confirming delivery for: a desk and desk chair. Guess what? After bringing the desk to the door they went back down stating, “we will bring the chair.” No joke after three confirmations about the desk and chair, they walk up with, SURPRISE, the sofa table I tried relentlessly to cancel that had not once been confirmed for delivery. The best resolution I could get at this time was the sales person no longer worked at that store. Unfortunately that wasn’t the end. Within a few months of regular wear, the table set and my entertainment center started cracking. Everything takes a small break here due to covid, however I had called in January and was told “someone would get back with me”. (That didn’t happen and by February we all had more important things to do). Called back in May as my state is slow-opening. When I did get ahold of someone they were very polite and had an appraiser come out in a reasonable time. The appraiser wore a mask and was very professional. The paperwork that ended up getting approved in our claim was for my table set and my entertainment center to be replaced. Had the replacements come without a hiccup, I would not have been motivated to write this review. Unfortunately, the team that arrived to replace the furniture walked in with one table leg to replace the one that had completely fallen off the table. I had to be very firm about getting the whole set replaced with two men who were already in my house trying to fix one leg. Begrudgingly, (yes begrudgingly) and after a statement by one of them that “If they replace the whole table they won’t have a new one to sell” they finally brought in a table to assemble. They then tried to not replace the broken chairs. I again was put into a position where I had to argue with two grown men, inside my own house, about their own work order which stated that they needed to replace the whole set. The work order that they received before being dispatched. Anyway, they replaced 4 broken chairs with nice chairs and replaced the two that weren’t broken with the most wobbly chairs I have ever seen. The legs are off in size by about 5cm of each-other. It was so noticeable that one of the team members remarked “oh, those probably need to be adjusted”, before he said bye and walked out. I waited a day to cool off before calling to explain what happened, and the response I got from the first person I spoke too was that “It sounded like I received the services that were requested,” and she, “Doesn’t see what the current issue is.” I didn’t bother mentioning to the next person that their team members had blatantly tried to cheat me for the company or for themselves on the side, and just requested that they replace the chairs that never should have been brought here in the first place. TL:DR This store will be very happy to take the money you spend on furniture, then try very hard to never ever speak to you again. If you succeed to speak with someone who cares about your problem, it’s probably because they have a backup plan to screw you with the dispatch teams they send to fix it.

I went in with my husband to buy some stuff for my house, the guy that we ask for help did help us. Ok, I appreciate the help. My problem is, when he said my delivery will come on the second week of April or the ending, but no. Quarantine happen, nobody call to let us know that there store is closing. I live about an hour and half from Tucson and I understand that they were closing down. It's almost 2 months and I never heard from them, until I called them last week and found out they were temporary shut down. Today, I called in since the voicemail said they will be opening back up today, a lady name Adhga answer and was very rude. I ask her that I didn't know they were closing down and she said oh yeah we were shut down and I said ok, I'm trying to find out about my order because apparently it was supposed to be delivery last week or the week before then I ask her, aren't you guys supposed to let the customer know that there orders are pending or delivery date is push back, you know just heads up. And all she said was, let me check your order. She didn't take the time to listen, no apologize which is what I didn't really care much about it but at least be more professional about it. She ask me if I want to schedule for a delivery, I said yes and she said ok that will be the 14th of May...It's not like it's a $20 order; not everyone have that kind of money to throw around...if I didn't needed it, I would've canceled it. Ok so I'm going to put a 3 star because of Shannon or Susan from delivery. Again I don't write stuff like this unless its neccessary. To the manager who call me the 4th of this month and said will call back, thanks for trying to help. It's ok you dont have to call back. I already talk to Shannon and she was very helpful and she is scheduling my order on the 14th. Have a good day!

We feel disappointed and underwhelmed by Sam Levitz/Ashley. The sales people were great but the mattress and adjustable base that we bought Wednesday failed to show up Friday as promised and we had to go to the store to find out what happened as no one called us back-Even after 3 phone calls and a online chat with customer service! We then rented a trailer to go pick it up ourselves and they said they had shipped the mattress to another store on the far side of town.A different manager then promised our item would be delivered on Sunday....they didn’t show up! Another manager called Monday and was going to sort out the issue and call the next day, but called 2 days later and promised again we would see our new mattress by Friday( a week after promised). After they didn’t show we went in and got our money back...We are new to town and just bought a house and couldn't have felt worse about our choice to shop there . We only live 5 minutes from the store and didn’t think shopping for a mattress would be so difficult from a company that promises in every ad we see,read, hear that they have next day delivery. What a waste of time....

Went into Ashley HomeStore East to buy furniture for my new build and was greeted by a gentleman and was abandoned shortly after. I ran into Harley and asked if she could help me and don’t mentioned that I don’t know where my sales person was. She asked what I needed and my style. I worked collaboratively with Harley Recklau to fulfill my needs. She took notes and showed me everything to fit my style. She also suggested the Home Gallery even though it wasn’t her store and could lose out on a sale. The gentleman that was initially my sales person seen the list Harley wrote down with SKU number and he decided to come by to make an appearance after 2 hours of me being there. I left due to them closing and told Harley I will be back once I close on my new build to purchase my items. My husband went to the Home Gallery and found these amazing flexsteel couches that Harley recommended to meet our needs. Harley kept me posted via email and after we closed like promised I went in and bought my furniture from Harley including my flexsteel couches. It’s not everyday you come into contact with someone so caring and patient. I have a 4 year old and she treated my daughter like if it was her own grand baby. For anyone looking to buy anything from Ashley HomeStore; Harley will take care of you even after delivery. We had a minor issue with one of the couches as they delivered a damaged floor model. I reached out to Harley and she contacted the delivery manager and we received the brand new couch within 2 hours. The delivery guys were so pleasant and so sociable. We never had this kind of experience before and we are truly blessed.

Worst customer experience I have ever had. First nobody told me when my items came in, then last minute they couldn’t deliver to my apartment because one of the parts was out of stock. Then they rescheduled the delivery on a day/time I told them not to. That morning they called to reschedule because they claimed that the headboard I ordered was suddenly out of stock, then they called back a few hours later to tell me that they “found” one. Then when they got to my apartment, the same part they originally told me was out of stock was still out of stock and they couldn’t attach my headboard. I returned the headboard and they did give me a refund, but only a month later after multiple calls. I got a new headboard from somewhere else, and couldn’t even attach it at first because the people who delivered my bed frame put it together crooked and incorrectly. It took me 5 hours to attach everything. I will never again shop at Ashley furniture, and have been telling people I know not to shop here either. I have never experienced such a severe lack of professionalism and reliability

On 14 June 2019 we purchased a 5 piece bedroom suite and a dining room set from the Tucson location. We were informed that the dining room chairs were not in stock but would be available and delivered on Saturday, 29 June; okay, no big deal. Then we were informed that the bedroom suite was not complete but via manager approval they would "hijack" someone else's order to complete mine. Saturday, 15 June. The bedroom suite and dining room table arrived. The crew assembled and did a great job!! Saturday, 29 June. I never received a phone call, text or email regarding the dining room chairs. I contacted Levitz delivery and I was informed that 2 of the 4 chairs were available for delivery. "Why are you calling and scheduling delivery" my wife asks. "good question" I answered. I called Ashley Home Store. I spoke to a sales manager (sorry, but I forgot his name) as to why there has been no contact with me regarding the chairs. He apologized and said he will look into it. He continues to explain that they are limited to supply from California. I counter with "if the chairs are available at another store (Phoenix) I will drive up to retrieve them". Turns out each store is independent. Sales manager promises to have them by 13 July. I receive a phone call the week of the 10th saying that we are scheduled for delivery between noon and 4pm on Saturday, 13 July. Groovy. Saturday, 13 July at around 3:30, I receive a phone call saying that the delivery guys are running late and that we can expect them around 5:30. I inform the caller that we had scheduled our day around your delivery schedule. "Reschedule for Monday, 15 July" I said. I accepted the 8 to 12 time frame. Monday, 15 July, 11:30. Delivery truck shows up with the chairs and to be honest, we completely forgot what they looked like. The moral to this story is, if you are going to buy from this store (because I can not comment on other Ashley stores) do yourself a favor and make sure that all components of your purchase are in stock.

I had walked through the store for a few good minutes. In my head I wondered when I would look lost enough to get some help. Finally a gentleman walked to me and asked if I needed help, and I said yes, she then called Vanessa who was finishing up with a previous client. She gracefully approached me and my daughters, made us all feel at home and comfortable. She gave my daughters balloons and then started taking care of business 'that was the order I would wish to recieve care'. She was selfless (double checked and triple checked numbers, deals, options and combinations to fit our budget), she never tried to push a sale, she was patient with my changes where necessary because I needed to fit a few more things in my small budget for the carehome, she is all smiles constantly and very relatable. Just the person you want to meet at the store to take away the pressure of budgeting and geting the best quality stuff in a well groomed budget. Since I have plenty more to busy for my carehome business, Vanessa gives me the courage to go back to Sam's because she will find the best stuff to suit my budget. I highly recommend her for service and customer care. She will smile all the time but most of all have you leave gratified.

I dont know how Sam Levitz recieved 5 stars. The sales team must be asking for them. If i could give them 0 stars i would. Their entire set up gives Ashley's a bad name. They're unorganized with their deliver dates/times, they're sales team is extremely pushy (if they even acknowledge you) and they're customer service team is extremely rude. My first time shopping with Sam Levitz was when i first moved to Tucson. I was in desperate need of a couch so i went to Sam levitz picked out my couch and left. The sales girl was super pushy and wanted me to open and in house account, politely declined. I paid for my couch cash, made sure the deliver date and color was right and left. When my couch arrived it was a completely different couch and color. I went to another location on Prince to get assistance with the delivered couch - know one help me. So i went to the location on Pantano Rd. and was told the right couch would arrive in two weeks. I received a call later saying the couch wasnt going to arrive on time and they didn't have a for sure date. I cancelled my order and purchase a couch from French connection. I tried their Pontano location when i needed a new matress and bedroom set. I found items that i liked was ready to complete my purchase but the sales guy kept trying to sale me sheets. I left so annoyed and sick from the motion of a matress he tried to sell me, I didnt even purchase the matress and bedroom set from the store. I decided to got home and purchase my matress from a different company and my bedroom set from the online ashley stores. To my dismay, my order ended up at the pantano store. I place my order on the 28 of jan and recieved an expected delivery date of 17 Feb. I was told on the 13 that my items wouldn't be delivered until the end of the month and they could give me an exact date. Three times is enough. I have ordered from Ashley's while living in other states and i have never experienced this type of customer service (or lack there of). Folks, take your cash to the french connection if you have to choose a tucson store. You'll pay a little more but you wont have to sleep on the floor because Sam Levitz dosent have their stuff together.

Sammie was great! She was there when we needed her but didn't hover or pressure us. This isn't our first purchase there and it won't be our last. Nice selection and friendly, helpful staff...........This portion has been added for the scheduling and delivery: We ordered an entertainment center with a fireplace insert and they called to schedule delivery but only had a portion of what we ordered. When we purchased the items we asked for a Saturday delivery and that all items be delivered at the she time. Makes sense because we have to tear down the old entertainment center and move furniture around for the new delivery. We also said that if we had to wait longer for this to happen it wouldn't be a problem. After we turned down delivery the first time they called with an incomplete order they called again and it appeared at a glance to be complete. I was wrong because the actual TV stand portion of the entertainment center was not on the paper but to make it worse when they did show up for delivery they only brought the fire place insert. We now had to put the living room and old entertainment center back together. Two weeks later they delivered everything complete. The delivery guy/assembler was just great but everything in-between the sale and final delivery was horrible. They didn't seem to care very much about this botched purchase so here it is for the public to view and come to their own conclusions on wether to purchase from Ashley's or elsewhere.

Horrible customer service when it came to delivery. I asked for the delivery to be from 4-8 on Monday. Before noon on Monday they were at my house, I told them to come back I cant take it. Dispatch called and confirmed there was a mistake and offered $150 off if I would take the delivery. I couldnt. So I called them back and I was told they would be at my house between 4-4:10. 5 comes around and nothing so I call again and Im told now it wont be til after 540. Well since I was told 4-410 I made arrangements to get my kids by that time. So I cancelled and rescheduled for once agian between 4-8 Tuesday. 11:30 Tuesday I get a call that they are on their way I said no it has to be after 4 the time I scheduled it for, they got snippy and told me if I cant take it before 4 I need to reschedule. So I got off the phone called a manager and told him what was going on he said he would take care of it. About 30 mins later dispatch called and confirmed delivery after 4, then the manager called and also confirmed after 4.... well at about 245 guess who is at my door...... Yep the delivery! I told him the time is scheduled for after 4 and they need to come back, he said “well we are here now” i told him thats not my problem I confirmed after 4 with management already. He asked why I cant take it now I told him it doesnt matter I set up after 4 delivery and thats when Ill accept it. He told me “what should be do, just wait in the truck?” Not my problem. I called and spoke to a manager again and now I am upset that a person who is supposed to enter my home has been so rude to me that I just cancel everything, I no longer want the table. I get an apology and okay. Now at 324 I get a call from the manager saying the truck just did another delivery and can be back at 4 if I want to change my mind. No! I am not letting some rude jerks in my house. I go to one of the room in my house and see something on the sidewalk so I open the front door and they unloaded everything and left it in front of my door and down the walk way! I have to leave at 330 to get my kids and I cant, Im blocked in and The truck is behind my car. So they never left my house, they tried to prove some point about being here right at 4 and having everything unloaded. Are you kidding me?!? I call the manager again and this time listen to him speak with the ppl in charge of deliveries and get another apology whatever And then Im told that after 6 he will call me back to confirm everything was cancelled. Well that never happened I called them Thursday to make sure and guess what.... they offered to delivery it again! It was never cancelled. What a joke! 8 calls on Monday and 11 calls on Tueaday followed by MY follow up on Thursday all for a table I never got.

It's meh quality furniture for more than it's worth. If that's not bad enough, there is no semblance of accurate inventory. I went in to buy furniture, and the initial sales associate told me that EVERYTHING I ordered was in stock, minus a couple of things for the spare bedrooms. The same sales associate forgot to add a couch, love seat, chair and kitchen table to my initial order as well, which required a second visit. When I received the delivery notice, the only things being delivered, were the items I bought the second time I went. As far as the sales people (vultures) go, the first one got me most of my stuff, but not all of it, which required a second visit. The second time around, I was helped by the receptionist Lien N. She was very customer service oriented, and had an amazing personality that made shopping for furniture an enjoyable process. After the sale, she kept up with my order, informed me if anything changed, and made sure that my order was scheduled that everything was good to go. I wouldn't recommend anyone go to Ashley or Sam Levitz, but if you do decide to go, I would seek out Lien N., she will take care of you, and you will have fun in the process. One last thing. People walk in to either look or buy. With so many vultures around, not one person needs to be asked if they need any help. Trust me, if a customer needs help, has a question, or wants to buy something, all they have to do is turn around and they will see a "sales associate" lurking in the shadows....staring....waiting....slowly moving in to feast upon the prey that unwittingly wandered in to the pit of woe. That's my honest review. Take it or leave it, I do not care. The manager did "upgrade" my mattress due to the manager lying about a phantom inbound shipment of mattresses that I was initially told was in stock. If it wasn't for Lien and her amazing customer service, and that mattress being comfy, I'd write a program to give this place negative stars. Happy shopping and good luck if you decide to shop there.

I talked to the sell’s person Anthony, and scheduled a same day appointment to drive all the way from Sierra Vista to see him for a bedroom set. When I entered the store with my service dog, I asked for Anthony; the first thing he told me was “is that a service dog?” I said yes. He rolled his eyes and told me what kind of service he provides? I told him that it would be my medical condition and I don’t think you are allowed to ask me that. He told me: “yes I can”. I told him I won’t share that information with you but I will show you the paperwork from VA that proves my dog’s title. I went to my truck and got the paperwork and went back inside the store and asked for the manger. He told me that is their job and they are obligated by their corporate to ask that question. I showed them the paperwork and they accepted it. Unfortunately I was too upset to do my business at that store. I just left and would never go back. For 6 years I have been Ashley’s customer and purchased quite a few pieces of furniture from them; and I must say I never were treated so poorly. They talk the talk when it comes to supporting veterans but if you require a service animal they expose you and treat you like dirt. Nice work!
